            <title>[CASSANDRA-5341] Select writetime  Exception when  data doesn&apos;t exist</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5341</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I try do to a &#8220;select writetime&#8221; on a empty column, I have an Exception. &lt;br/&gt;
For example : &lt;br/&gt;
Create table test (id  int, value int, value2 int, primary key (id));	&lt;br/&gt;
INSERT INTO test (id, value ) VALUES ( 1,100) ;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;select * from test where id =1; &lt;br/&gt;
==&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 id | value | value2&lt;br/&gt;
---&lt;del&gt;&lt;ins&gt;&lt;/del&gt;-----&lt;del&gt;&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/del&gt;-------&lt;br/&gt;
  1 |   100 |   null	&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&#8217;s working.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;select WRITETIME(value) from test where id =1; &lt;br/&gt;
==&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 writetime(value)&lt;br/&gt;
------------------&lt;br/&gt;
 1363184789539000&lt;br/&gt;
It&#8217;s working&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;select WRITETIME(value2) from test where id =1; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;==&amp;gt;TSocket read 0 bytes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have an Exception.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
